A 22-year-old man was found dead in apparent suicide in Loikas, Samburu County. Samburu Central sub-county police commandant Alex Rotich said HIV self-testing kit showing positive result was found near the victim’s body. The victim allegedly hanged himself using a belt in his rented room. Mr Rotich said there was no suicide note but the test kit found at the scene were used and had blood stains. "The test kits had blood stains. He might have repeated the test more than twice," Mr Rotich said. The body of the deceased was taken to Samburu County Referral Hospital mortuary for a post-mortem examination. Following the incident, the police boss urged religious leaders to guide the young generation accordingly because suicide cases have increased in the region in the recent past. 